metadata.name: The Statue of Pepe Zeus
metadata.description:
The Statue of Zeus at Olympia was a giant seated figure, about 12.4 m tall.
Made by the Greek sculptor Pepephidias around 435 BC at the sanctuary of Olympia, Greece, and erected in the Temple of PepeZeus there. PepeZeus is the sky and thunder god in ancient Greek religion, who rules as king of the gods of Mount PepeOlympus.

4000x4000 px
